<p>Meta is a technology company formerly known as Facebook, Inc. It rebranded to Meta Platforms, Inc. on October 28, 2021, to focus on building the metaverse, a collective virtual shared space created by the convergence of virtually enhanced physical reality and physically persistent virtual reality.</p><p><br /></p><p>Meta operates several major platforms and services including:</p><p>- Facebook: A social media platform for connecting with friends and family, sharing updates, and participating in various communities.</p><p>- Instagram: A photo and video sharing platform with features like Stories, Reels, and IGTV.</p><p>- WhatsApp: A messaging app that supports text, voice, and video communication, as well as file sharing.</p><p>- Messenger: A messaging app integrated with Facebook for text, voice, and video communication.</p><p>- Oculus: A virtual reality hardware and software company known for its VR headsets and related technology, acquired by Facebook in 2014.</p><p><br /></p><p>The company's vision involves developing the metaverse, a virtual environment where people can interact with each other and digital objects using technologies such as virtual reality (VR) and augmented reality (AR).</p><p><br /></p><p>Meta is engaged in initiatives to support its metaverse vision, including advancements in VR and AR technology, social platforms, and digital commerce. The company faces challenges and controversies related to privacy, data security, and content moderation, and continues to evolve its products and strategies in response to user needs and regulatory environments.</p>
